S NEW IN THIS CHECKPOINT{\*\bkmkend _Toc389469601}
\par }\pard\plain \sa120\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\b 1.4.10
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls25\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls25\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added the ability to do CDS log recovery to a select set of tables rather than the entire database.  This is accomplished by listing the tables to recover in the 'apply log' file.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Corrected bugs in the system-failure recovery logic.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}The setup data is no longer split into diskette size pieces.  It must be run from a CD-ROM or hard disk. 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Patches are now easily added to the distribution via a patch.bat in directory disk1.
\par }\pard\plain \sa120\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\b 
\par 1.4.9\tab 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls16\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls16\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
The setup script was changed to not install msvcrt40.dll, which was causing problems on Win95 systems.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}The setup s
cript was changed to accommodate the option of not installing the dictionary tools which are also available in the rt package.   If you use the rt package, it is better to install the dictionary tools from that package only.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}The setup script was changed to accommodate the option of installing only the client side utility programs, like cdsstat.exe and not the server programs like cdsv.exe. 

\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}The server configuration program, svrcfg.exe, was improved to hide advanced options unless requested by the user.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Bug Fixes.
\par }\pard \s32\widctlpar\adjustright {
\par }\pard\plain \sa120\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\b 1.4.8\tab }{This checkpoint was skipped. 
\par }{\b 1.4.7
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls7\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls7\adjustright {
Two-phase-commit functions as it should.   In previous versions, two-phase commit worked only on Unix servers.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls7\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls7\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
\f0 Cdinstsv.exe has a new option to list the installed servers in one line per server.  This list includes UDP port numbers.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard\plain \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls7\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls7\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {
ALTER TABLE supports adding or dropping column definitions.  This can be used to enable third party reporting tools like Crystal Reports and MS Access to read variable schema CDS tables.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls7\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls7\adjustright {
Batch insert is used by the ODBC interface and by QL when copying table records.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls7\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls7\adjustright {
Svrcfg, the cdserver configuration program invoked by the install process will warn you of attempts to use a single UDP port number for more than one server on NT.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls7\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls7\adjustright {
WordView is not installed with this package.  The WordView package is include on the CD-ROM with this CDS package and you may install it if you need it to read the CDS documentation.   You may use Micro
soft Word instead.  If you are on Windows 95 or Windows NT 4.0 or later, you can use WordPad, which come with the O/S.
\par }\pard\plain \s1\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f1\fs28\kerning28\cgrid {{\*\bkmkstart _Toc389469602}WHAT\rquote S NEW IN THIS RELEASE{\*\bkmkend _Toc316106367}{\*\bkmkend _Toc316106689}{\*\bkmkend _Toc316107074}
