\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3\fs20\cgrid \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li1080\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {New selection criteria comparators:  is_}{\b 
not_null; is null}{; [SQL] }{\b like }{pattern match; and }{\b not_like}{ pattern match.  These are available through QL.exe and CDS OFB verbs.  They are available with a slightly different syntax via ODBC.
