\par }\pard\plain \qj\keep\keepn\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {The following steps must be taken to install mosaic OA CDS.
\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {
Install Microsoft Windows NT or Microsoft Windows NT Server or Window 95.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {Set up and configure TCP/IP.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 3)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {If yo
ur machine is using a Domain Name Server, your machine must be registered with that DNS,  - or -
\par }\pard \qj\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl12\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\ilvl12\adjustright {You must have an entry in the }{\b\i hosts}{ file for the machine upon which you are installing.  That is the machine must have an entry in its }{\b\i 
hosts}{ file for itself.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 4)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {If you don\rquote 
t already have your data dictionary on the target machine, copy your moa data dictionary from a work station to the server machine.  You may need to create directories to do this.   The install process creates a test dictionary named \lquote min\rquote  i
f you don\rquote t use the customization choice dialog to deselect \lquote sample programs\rquote .  
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 5)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {
For each  CDS server that is running, truncate the recovery log file with cdsclrlg.exe.   The old log files may hold recovery records that are incompatible with the new se
rver.   For each server that is not running, delete its old recovery log file, which is usually named \lquote cds_log\rquote .
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 6)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {On NT, run \lquote cdinstsv -all stop\rquote 
 to stop all old CDS servers, if any,  in the services manager database.   This allows cdsv.exe to be replaced, it will }{\i not }{delete your data!! }{\b\fs22 You must logged on as a member of the administrators group}{
!   If you are changing MOADIR or MOAPROJ, run: \lquote cdinstsv \endash all remove\rquote  instead to remove all of the old CDS entries in the services manager database.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 7)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {If you ha
ve an existing dictionary from V3, delete all of the related ddtime files [\\moaproj\\*\\*cds*\\ddtime].  The install puts newly required fields into your data dictionary.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 8)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {
If you previously installed so that you have a remove option for this package in }{\fs22 My Computer/ Control Panel / Add-Remove}{
, run the remove/uninstall to properly decrement the registry counts of shared files.   Note that UnInstall is not supported on Windows NT 3.51.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 9)\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright {
If you are running on Window NT 3.51, you may wish to install WordView 
at this point, to enable you to read the CDS documentation, which is in Microsoft Word 6.0/95 format.   The WordView package is included on the CD-ROM with the CDS package.  It is not installed automatically.  To install WordView: cd \\wordview\\
disk1 and run setup.exe.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s16 \fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 10)\tab}}\pard\plain \s16\qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls2\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls2\adjustright \f6\fs20\cgrid {\f0 Install }{
\b\f0 mosaic OA }{\f0 Central Data Server..   }{\b\f0 On NT you must logged on as a member of the administrators group.}{\b  }{\f0 If you have existing CDS application tables, they will}{\i\f0  not}{\f0  b
e changed and they will remain accessible.   New entries may be added to the table of tables and the table of indexes to accommodate the new \lquote fields\rquote 
 table.   New entries may also be added to the field table in your project data dictionary to accommodate the fields table and the ODBC interface. }{\b  }{\f0 
\par }\pard \s16\qj\li360\keep\keepn\widctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\b   }{\f0 
\par From local CD_ROM or network (letter) mapped drive:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s16 \fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 a)\tab}}\pard \s16\qj\fi-360\li1440\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls3\pnrnot0\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls3\adjustright {\f0 
Run SRVSETUP.BAT to install CDS server package V1.4.5. 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s16 \fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 b)\tab}}\pard \s16\qj\fi-360\li1440\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls3\pnrnot0\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls3\adjustright {\f0 
If you are installing for emergency journalling on a workstation, use the custom installation option and deselect moa Message Switch (moamsw). 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s16 \fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 c)\tab}}\pard \s16\qj\fi-360\li1440\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls3\pnrnot0\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta )}}\ls3\adjustright {\f0 
