\par }\pard \s16\qj\li360\keep\keepn\widctlpar\ilvl12\adjustright {\b\f0\fs24 Windows 95 setup bugs work-around:}{\f0  
\par 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s16 \fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1.\tab}}\pard \s16\qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls5\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\ls5\adjustright {\f0 
Make sure DNS has correct IP address for your machine.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s16 \fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2.\tab}}\pard \s16\qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls5\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\ls5\adjustright {\f0 
If DNS is not present or not correctable, update your windows\\}{\b\f0 hosts }{\f0 file. If you have no windows\\hosts file copy \\windows\\hosts.sam to \\windows\\hosts. Then create an entry for your machine in the hosts file.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s16 \fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 3.\tab}}\pard \s16\qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls5\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\ls5\adjustright {\f0 
Make sure that the new field definitions are in your dictionary with \lquote findobj -nYourProject common:DomainName\rquote .   You will see \ldblquote findobj: Can't find object\rdblquote  if the new definitions are missing.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s16 \fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 4.\tab}}\pard \s16\qj\fi-360\li720\keep\keepn\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls5\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\ls5\adjustright {\f0 
If you install a second sever process on one machine, be sure to use a non-default UDP port address for one of the servers.  The servers won\rquote t work with a shared UDP port number on Windows 95.
