[CDS{\*\bkmkend _Toc301770796}{\*\bkmkend _Toc301771286}{\*\bkmkend _Toc302440481}{\*\bkmkend _Toc303665103}{\*\bkmkend _Toc304335361}]
\par }\pard\plain \li720\sa120\widctlpar\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {For each cdserver there may be a section in the .ini file.  The section name is: }{\b cds}{SERVNAME, where }{\b cds}{
 is a constant and SERVNAME is the optional service name suffix of the server, like}{\i  main}{ or }{\i cl}{.
\par }\pard \fi-2016\li3456\sa120\widctlpar\adjustright {\b CDS_PRIMARY_NP}{\tab The name of the designated primary or only NT machine that runs cdserver.   Default is to use UDP broadcast search for the server.    }{\b 
The default is usually fine for customer installation but it is perilous in a development environment because you may randomly connect to someone else\rquote s server with the same service name in your LAN.}{
\par }{\b CDS_SHADOW_NP}{\tab Needed only for resilient (UNIX server) systems. The name of the designated resilient shadow machine or }{\i none}{. (must be lower case \lquote none\rquote )
\par }{\b CDS_DIRECTORY}{\tab Needed only when cdserver runs on an NT machine and only if the default is not taken.  The default is a subdirectory within the dictionary directory.
\par }{\b CDS_LOG_PATH}{\tab Path to the recover log file.  Needed only when the default \ldblquote cds_log\rdblquote   is not wanted.  The only reason to set this is to get the recovery log on a separate disk drive.
\par }{\b CDS_NWLOG}{\tab Optional MCN debug logging mask, for debugging only.
