\par When you run a Winsock application (such as CDS or its clients), your Internet provider (such as The Microsoft Network) sign-in screen may appear. This behavior occurs when you have a network adapter and a modem installed in your
 computer and the AutoDial feature is enabled
\par RESOLUTION 
\par 
\par }\pard \qj\li720\widctlpar\adjustright {To prevent this behavior from occurring, follow these steps: 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1.\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li1080\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx1080{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls20\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\ls20\adjustright {
Use the right mouse button to click the Internet icon on your desktop, and then click Properties on the menu that appears.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2.\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li1080\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx1080{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls20\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\ls20\adjustright {
Click the Use AutoDial check box to clear it. 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\fs20\cgrid \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 3.\tab}}\pard \qj\fi-360\li1080\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx1080{\*\pn \pnlvlbody\ilvl0\ls20\pnrnot0\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxta .}}\ls20\adjustright {Click OK. 
\par }\pard \qj\li720\widctlpar\adjustright {
\par When you want Internet access, connect using The Microsoft Network desktop icon or your Internet provider icon. 
\par 
\par }\pard \qj\widctlpar\adjustright {When upgrading from version 1.3, moa message switch server (moamsw) usually cra
shes during the install process.   If this brings up Dr. Watson, simply clear it and continue.   This is a known bug in version 1.3 of moamsw.exe and the install process replaces it with a new version.
\par 
\par QL will not attempt to use the pager, even on ql comm
ands that request the pager.  This is due to a bug in Microsoft Visual C++ 4.2 which generally does not properly support the popen function.  Microsoft is working on this problem.  We recommend that the ql user resize the command window and use the scroll
 bar until a future release makes the pager again available.
\par 
\par A CDS client cannot access tables created by other clients unless those tables were created before the client connected to the database server.  This sometimes gives odd results.  For example: 
\par \tab \ldblquote select prime_key from X \ldblquote   gives \ldblquote table X does not exist\rdblquote 
\par     immediately followed by:
\par \tab \ldblquote create table X (prime_key int primary key)\rdblquote   gives \ldblquote Attempt to create duplicate table X\rdblquote .
\par 
\par Moa Investigator print function fails on Windows NT 4.0.
\par 
\par Documentation about required nightly administration of the CDS server on NT is not clear.
\par \page 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright \b\f1\fs28\kerning28\cgrid {{\*\bkmkstart _Toc337026038}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc359293559}{\*\bkmkstart _Toc389469619}CHANGE LOG}{\f2 {\*\bkmkend _Toc337026038}{\*\bkmkend _Toc359293559}
{\*\bkmkend _Toc389469619}
\par }\pard\plain \qc\ri-720\sa120\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw60\brsp20 \adjustright \fs20\cgrid {\b\fs24 Mosaic OA Central Data Server "Change & Enhancement" Log
