\par }\pard \qc\ri-720\sa120\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw60\brsp20 \adjustright {\fs24 Listed below are all changes implemented in version }{\b\fs24 4.10
\par }{\fs24 of the }{\b\fs24 mosaic OA}{\fs24  Central Data Server
\par &
\par Console Tools  P/N: }{\b\fs24 85-35011-D02}{\fs24 
\par }\pard \ri-720\sa120\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw60\brsp20 \adjustright {\fs24 
\par }\pard \qc\ri-720\sa120\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw60\brsp20 \adjustright {\i Note: These changes are listed in chronological order beginning with the latest changes listed first.
\par }\pard \ri-720\sa120\widctlpar\box\brdrs\brdrw60\brsp20 \adjustright {\f2 
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {8-4-97 CDSV smatch/rmatch fix (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls26\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls26\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed a problem where the server would crash when trying to compare a non-character field with a smatch/rmatch pattern. PTR#: 97070901, Files:optbl.c
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {8-1-97 CDSV rename table fix (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls26\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls26\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Rename table did not change the internal file name.  This lead to the potential of trying to create duplicate file names or worse!  Rename now computes the new internal file name based on the new table name.  Files: cdstable.c
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {7-28-97 CDSV enhancement, misc. fixes (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls26\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls26\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added the ability to do CDS log r
ecovery to a select set of tables rather than the entire database.  This is accomplished by listing the tables to recover in the apply log file.  See the CDS notes for more information on this feature. Files: cdsv.c, rollfor.c, rollback.c, cdsinit.c, cdsl
og.c, logread.c \endash  PTR#95111103
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed a recently introduced problem where CDS would not properly recover a replace with index change. Rollfor.c
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed a problem where CDS would not process rollbacks during recovery. Rollback.c
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed a problem where CDS would complain of a bad log when applying a log that contained create table commands. Logread.c
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \ilvl12\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {7-18-97 CDSV.exe Fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls26\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls26\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug which caused a NOT match operation to become a MATCH operation when the pattern was a simple string with no pattern characters.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {7-8-97 moa\\src\\MAKEFILE change (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls26\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls26\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Removed CDS package specific makes and moved them to MakeCDS  to avoid getting the wrong part numbers.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl12\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\ilvl12\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-26-97 CDSV minor fixes/enhancements (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls26\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls26\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
out file now contains explicit message when NT application event log is full. File: cdsfatal.c
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed an obscure problem that could cause a cds 1855 error.  Problem would happen when RT has an empty FIXED field (defined with no decimal places \endash 
 eg: 5.0), increments the field by 0.5, and attempts to insert it into CDS. File: tablist.c, PTR# 96050601
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \ilvl12\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-25-97 CDS client change (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls26\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls26\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
cds_udp_port() now returns a negative if it fails rather than calling an exit function (ersysn()).  So now calling programs should check for an error and handle it.  The function cds_udp_port() is exposed in cdscl.dll.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl12\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\ilvl12\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-25-97 CDS install fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls26\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls26\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Close the program group window before finishing so it won't obscure the completion message.
\par }\pard\plain \sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl12\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\ilvl12\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {
\par }{\b\fs24\ul 6-24-97 CDS and CDSODBC R1V4 Checkpoint 9 Complete\tab }{\b\fs24 
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-20-97 CDS install fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls21\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls21\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Run Drop-1A.exe on NT machines to get rid of control-Z characters at the end of \\etc\\services before running svrcfg.exe to update that file.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-20-97 CDS fix for more recovery problems (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls21\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls21\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Don't crash rolling forward a drop table when the table to be dropped already doesn\rquote t exist.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Allow three days of out file instead of only two before discarding it on open.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-16-97 CDS fix for duplicate record problem (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls22\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls22\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed a problem where CDServer could create duplicate records in the database.  The specific problem occurred when CDS recovered after a record replace followed by a replace
 with index change on the same record.  CDS compression can be used to remove the duplicate records after the index is rebuilt.  PTR# 97052901, files: rollfor.c
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-11-97 SVRCFG (CDS configurator) Fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls23\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls23\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed problems dealing with service name suffixes}{\ul 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}{Use lower case for CDS section names in ddproj.ini
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-6-97 QL.exe Fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls24\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls24\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Allow the date value "0" for backward compatibility.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {6-05-97 CDS Fix (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls25\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls25\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed a problem in CDS where CDS would terminate with an out file message: Caught signal 21 and Terminated by signal 21.  This problem was related to a user signing off of the server sometime after compression was run.  PTR# 97060402.  Files: cdscmprs.c

\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {5-28-97 CDS Fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls18\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed problem that caused crash in cdsv.exe when project name was longer than 30 characters.}{\ul 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls19\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls19\adjustright {
Changed package to not install msvcrt40.dll, to avoid problems on Win95.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls18\adjustright {
Fixed bugs in svrcfg.exe and svrcfgh.dll, the CDS configuration utility.  Made enhancements suggested by John Lowry:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard \s32\fi-360\li720\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls18\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls18\adjustright {
Provide a pick list for project name, based on subdirectories of MOAPROJDIR.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Hide advanced options unless called for by the user.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Show previously configured advanced options when reconfiguring a server.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fix bugs in showing previously configured UDP port number.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {5-15-97 CDS & RT header modules (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls17\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls17\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Removed cds_errno from rtdef.h.  It is no longer exported.  Use clenv.h instead.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Removed cds_errno as an export from cdserror.h.   It is no longer exported, as of checkpoint 8.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}There is a new function, CdsErrNo(clenv *env), exported by cdscl.dll, which returns the cds_errno value for an environment.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {V1.4.7 here
\par 4-7-97 CDS Table Rename When Using Multiple CDServers (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls16\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls16\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
When renaming a table while connecting to multiple CDServers, a duplicate table e
rror would be reported if the new table name existed on ANY of the CDServers.  Changed so that the name only has to be unique on the server with the table that is being renamed.  File: clstubs.c
\par }\pard\plain \sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {4-7-97 QL.EXE Data Length Validation (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls16\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls16\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
ql has been ch
anged to validate the length of data being inserted into CDS.  The default action for data larger than the defined field size is to report an error.  Optionally, ql can be set to truncate the excess data or to ignore the length validation and allow the da
ta into CDS. Files changed: ql.h, ql.c, qldml.c, qlaux.c.  PTR# 97030504 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Minor change to allow specific index to be displayed on table using named service specification (show indexes on service:table).  Files: ql.c, PTR#: 97032401
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {04-02-97 CDSV change (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls14\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls14\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Create a debug map from the link of cdsv.exe and put it in the distribution.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-21-97 CDS Enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls13\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls13\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
When cdsv is started from the command line it shows a minimized window only unless the command line option }{\b \endash W}{ is used.  This addresses PSR# 3968.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-20-97 CDS prcapture bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls13\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls13\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed print of statistics evoked by the \endash s command line option by using vsprintf() instead of wvsprintf() in misc\\hexdmp.c.   Only vsprintf() supports the %f format.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Get ticks per second from capture file, if available, so prcapture can accurately show the time used per function at the original server machine.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-18-97 CDS Enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls10\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls10\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added LIST option to cdinstsv.exe.  This is an abbreviated list of the VIEW info plus showing the UDP port number used. 
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-17-97 CDS Setup Fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls11\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls11\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Changed svrcfg.exe and svrcfgh.dll to accept only a full path for the cds recovery log file.   This fixes PSR 4000.   The program now tries to show the option previously chosen when re-configuring.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed svrcfg.exe handli
ng of UDP port numbers so that the existing previously configured port number for a server is preserved unless explicitly overridden by the developer.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed svrcfg.exe handling of UDP port numbers so that if a user specifies an existing previously conf
igured port number for a different server, that user gets a warning message and a chance to reconsider the port number.  This fixes PSR #4005.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls12\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls12\adjustright {
Changed svrcfg.exe to insist on a valid project name.  This fixes PSR #4037.
\par }\pard \s32\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright {
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-17-97 CDS ODBC Enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls10\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls10\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added support for SQL ALTER TABLE statement to allow developers to add or drop column definitions for a table.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}ALTER TABLE with ADD column is now supported for variable schema tables to allow use with third party reporting tools like Crystal Reports and MS Access.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-12-97 cdsstat.exe Enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls9\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls9\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added option \ldblquote \endash C\rdblquote  to show count of current connections.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-12-97 ql.exe Enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls9\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls9\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added SLEEP verb for use in testing scripts.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-12-97 Osql.exe Enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls9\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls9\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added SLEEP verb for use in testing scripts.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-12-97 ODB.DLL Fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls9\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls9\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fix bugs in setting column precision, especially for timestamp data.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added to dberrs.h #define MOA_PUT_EMPTY_STRING_AS_NULL 2202, option ID for DBsetConnectOption().
\par }\pard \s32\widctlpar\adjustright {
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-10-97 Osql.exe  changes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Allow semi-colon at end of tables, sqltables, and types requests.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Honor 'commit', 'rollback' and 'begin work' requests.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {3-5-97 CDSV Running as Service Fix (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed a problem where CDSV would fail to run as a service, reporting event information related to a different project than expected for the service.  PTR 97012302, Files: cdsv.c, start.c
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {03-05-97 CDSODBC.dll - Enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added support for inserting mulitple records, using bound parameter arrays.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added support for ODBC API function SQLParamOptions() as a part of the array insert support.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {03-04-97 ODB.dll - Enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
New client side option MOA_PUT_EMPTY_STRING_AS_NULL for DBsetConnectOption().  The default is FALSE, meaning FT_ASCII fields 
with empty string values are set to the database as a zero length string.  The trouble with this is that SQL-Server silently converts empty strings to single character blank strings.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-28-97 CDS import and export fix/enhancement (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Modified cdsimprt and cdsexprt to support connection to multiple servers.  See cds notes for more details on this feature.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added -T switch to cdsimprt to allow truncation of ascii and numeric data that exceeds defined field size.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Made cdsexprt and cdsimprt compatible w
ith previous versions.  Old export files can be imported on current version and export files from current version can be imported on older versions.  Files: imexport.h, cdsimprt.c, cdsexprt.c.  For PTRs: 97022703, 97022704, 97020501, 97012902.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-28-97 CDS setup bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Changed cdinstsv.exe to prevent install when MOAPROJDIR is a remote drive or a RAM drive.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed cdsv.exe to prevent logging of superfluous start and stop events.  In particular \ldblquote StartServiceCtrlDispatcher failed\rdblquote  information is 
no longer written.  It wasn\rquote t helpful.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-27-97 CDS bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Postpone checking for server running on designated machine to allow a mix of machine for different service name suffixes with the same dictionary.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed bug that caused crash in CDS ODBC driver when selecting with a very long projection list.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-27-97 CDS ODBC Enhancements (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Allow smalldatetype as a column data-type, meaning DATE
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Allow column definition option of NULL, which the default, meaning \lquote allow null value\rquote .
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}support error SQLState 21S01 when insert values list doesn\rquote t match the column list.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Give a more explicit error message when user tries to update current of cursor when that cursor was not defined with a FOR UPDATE clause in the select statement.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-27-97 CDS prcaptur.exe bug fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug that caused failure when -S option was used in the command line.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-25-97 CDS bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Use exclusive record update locks on ODBC fetches when reading on an updatable context within a LUW, when the SQL_TXN_ISOLATION option is SQL_TXN_READ_COMMITTED (the default) or higher.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}
Use exclusive lock inside the server when reading for Update_All() and currently in a LUW and current connection option for concurrency is SQL_TXN_READ_COMMITTED.  That option setting is the default 
for users of the CDS ODBC driver.   Users of the old interface may set that option too, via SetConnectOption(), but their default is SQL_TXN_READ_UNCOMMITTED.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Wrap the update in a LUW whenever not already in a LUW and the update is a Cds_Update_All() that could affect more than one record.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Set proper SQLState for bad option ID and bad option parm value for SQLSetConnectOption.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Make sure that SQL_TXN_ISOLATION option default value at the server is SQL_TXN_READ_COMMITTED.   (For ODBC clients only).
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added support for updating a column  to NULL value from ODBC.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Return correct SQLState when given a bad table name on an ODBC INSERT statement.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Return correct SQLState when given a bad primary key for an insert or a bad secondary key for any update.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-24-97 CDS QL bug fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Adjust at run time to not use batch insert on insert from select when the server can\rquote t handle it.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-21-97 CDS crash on find_n (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed a problem where CDS could crash on find_n if a previous find_n on the same context failed for some reason.  The example used to produce the failure was encountering an exclusive locked record. Files changed: cdsfind.c. PTR #97021301
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-21-97 CDS bug fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug that prevented the closing of a pseudo-connection created during restart general recovery for rollback of an incomplete LUW.   Changed only ccb.c.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-14-97 CDS Enhancements (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {\b\fs24 
Requests for EXCLUSIVE record locks are }{\b\i\fs24 silently}{\b\fs24  downgraded to simple update locks when the lock requests are outside of a Logical Unit of Work.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}{CDS ODBC SQL now supports insert from a query spec as well as from a values list.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-13-97 CDS Enhancements (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Ordinal numbers in SQL \lquote ORDER BY\rquote  clauses are now supported.  The ordinal number must refer to a column in the projection list.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-11-97 CDS Enhancements (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added batch insert function to client and server.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed QL to use batch insert when inserting from a selected context.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed CDSODBC driver to use batch insert for every insert.  The normal batch size is one.  The batch may contain as many records as will fit in one 64K buffer.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Allow multiple VALUES lists on an SQL insert statement to create multiple rows with one statement.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Allow TEXT as a data type specifier in a create table statement.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Allow user to use dictionary fields from up to 7 different dictionary applications, within a single SQL statement, such as CREATE TABLE.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {02-06-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added multi-thread support.   The driver is now \lquote thread safe\rquote .  Fixes PSR 4011.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Detect and report invalid date literals in SQL \lquote where\rquote  clauses.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Cleanup up some other error reporting to return the correct SQLState.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Change parser to allow table_name.index name in DROP INDEX table_name.index_name.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-31-97 CDS Two-Phase Commit Fixes (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Made fixes necessary f
or NT CDServer to pass the two-phase commit tests in the CDS regression test suite.  Prior to these changes, CDS would fail on all two phase commit or rollback attempts.  Changed both CDS and RT. Files: clstubs.c, cmfparms.c, cdslog.c, cds.c, ccb.c, svdof
unc.c, svsvproc.h, svinit.c, svunpack.c, servnt.c, server.c, svsetup.c.  PTR 96112001, 97011401.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-31-97 CDS 873 Causes RT to Crash (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Changed RT to not catastrophe on CDS 873 errors.  Application is now responsible for checking for such errors and taking appropriate action.  File: execcds.c, clstusbs.c.  PTR 96120601
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-31-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added function SQLNativeSql().  If the parser likes a statement it will return it via SQLNativeSql.   You still can\rquote t see what goes to server execept through prcaptur.exe.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed parser to recognize GRANT statements.  Nothing is done with them but now scripts with GRANTs in them can be executed without error.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-30-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
don't release the context created for an insert and don't create a new CDS context when the existing stmt->contxt will work for an insert.  This speeds performance on insert.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Announce that only one connection per user is allowed via SQLGetInfo(SQL_ACTIVE_CONNECTIONS).
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-28-97 LOGDUMP utility fix (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
The CDS logdump utility would crash or report incorrect information when processing some 2-phase commit log records.  It now reports those records properly.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-28-97 RT - do not catastrophe on CDS 873 errors (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {Change
d RT to not catastrophe on CDS 873 (CDS_NOT_IN_LUW) errors.  Any application request for rollback will result in a rollback at all the CDServers that the client is connected to.  The application is responsible for taking the proper action when a rollback 
occurs.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-28-97 ODB.dll - Fix DBbegin() to work with the above fix for LUWs. (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Changed DBbegin to work with new cdscl.dll changed in clstubs.c Cds_Rollback().
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-28-97 CDSV.exe bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug in displaying debug stuff before connect->ftab was setup.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed bug of incorrectly returning a value from a no_ret function.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-28-97 CDSODBC.dll bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bugs in parsing and handling hexadecimal (bulk) constants.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-27-97 CDSV.exe bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls8\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls8\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
stop ignoring lengths in comparison of two bulk values.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-22-97 mi.exe bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug that caused mi to crash on an assert in _spawnl() when attempting to run udpinfo.exe.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed bug that caused mi to not find udpinfo.exe when run from a directory where udpinfo.exe did not reside.    [both changes to module network.cpp only]
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-20-97 CDSV.exe bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bugs in handling next fetch on a cursor after an update that changed the key of the current record for the index used for the cursor.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-15-97 QL.exe (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug inserting from one table to another that cause creation of a context name that was too long.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {1-14-97 CBS.exe (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added and extra 3 bytes for each FT_FIXED decimal field.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {01-06-97 CDSV.exe fixes   (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Allow an 8 character suffix name with a 30 character project name.   Previous version allowed only a total of 34 characters.  Now allow a total of 58 characters.  Published, supported limit is 30 + 8.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Use a case insensitive name search when looking for duplicate table names.  Names weren\rquote t truly case insensitive since we moved to NT from unix.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {12-20-96 CDSV setup fixes and enhancements (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added an empty wrdview6.opt to the distribution to improve the uninstall.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed to not allow selection of moa message switch on win95.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Use c:\\temp, if it exists, as the working directory for moa investigator, to receive mi.log files.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {V1.4.4 checkpoint made here.
\par 12-18-96 CDSV setup fixes and enhancements (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug in svrcfg.exe that prevented upgrade of dictionary field tables with \lquote newflds\rquote  file.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed bug in svrcfg.exe that stopped the moa message switch server.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {12-09-96 CDSV Install fixes and enhancements (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed binary version number info in all programs.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed rcbump to correctly set the binary version number in _v.rc files.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed svrcfg.exe to work correctly with Windows 95.  
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {11-30-96 CDSreasn.exe bug fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug preventing print of last line in a segment of the out file.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {11-27-96 MKdist.mak ported to msvc 4. (s)
\par 11-27-96 setup.mak  files ported to msvc 4. (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
moasetup.mak  and moved files from setupcmn to moasetup directory.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}svrcfgh.mak
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}svrcfg.amk
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}ssetuph.mak
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}ssetup.mak
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {11-15-96 QL - disabled pager while popen broke in Visual C 4.2 (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
QL will not attempt to use the pager, even on ql commands that request the pager.  This is due to a problem in VC 4.2 that generally does not properly support the popen command.  Microsoft is working on this problem.  Recommend that t
he ql user resize the command window and use the scroll bar until the pager is again available. Changed ql.h, ql.c, qldml.c, and qlaux.c.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {11-09-96 CDS bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Terminate the heartbeat thread during MCNClose() if there are no more active connections.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Deregister the class used for the private window in all clients but rt.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {11-04-96 CDS bug fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed a V4 bug in cdsv.exe that caused the server to crash (unrecoverably!) during some node merges and some node split recovery logging.   The changed touched cbtree.h, cbtree.lib and cdscl.dll as well as cdsv.exe.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed a V4 bug in QL.exe that caused it to load incorrectly rotated values from ascii source for FT_IND fields.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {11-04-96 CDSexprt changes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
More descriptive and informative messages about failures, especially FT_IND translation failures.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Give a second chance on FT_IND translation failures, rotating the integer value before the second try.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {11-01-96 CDS changes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Changed cdsnight.cmd to include an option for an rdate server.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed cdsnight.cmd to use long enough sleep periods to allow the services manager to flush out its time-out queues before restarting or stopping cdsv.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed bug in cdsrtest.ksh to remove a dependency on the location of MOAPROJ.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added MFC42d.DLL to distribution for use by mi.exe.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {10-21-96 CDS fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed bug in handling superfluous table name qualifiers in selection criteria.  Example: select from TEST where TEST.common:mycolumn < 12.   In previous versions, table name qualifiers on column references were allowed only in join selection criteria.

\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed }{\b is_null}{ and }{\b is_not_null}{ to single operand operators, binding left.  Retained }{\b is_missing}{
 as allowing and sometimes requiring two operands, with the second operand being a meaningless placeholder.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {10-14-96 CDS enhancements and fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Enable a client to think it has multiple connections to a single server at one push level.  - Added a use count for each connect.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Enable a single client to connect to servers with different interface levels.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed a bug in prcapture\rquote s display of zero length decimal values.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed a bug in prcapture\rquote s display of hexadecimal (bulk) values, so that extra blank lines are not printed.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}New function clFreeEnv() destroys environment object created by clAllocEnv().
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {10-01-96 CDS fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added optional ANSI-SQL cursor fetch behavior.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}New, more flexible and backward compatible interface specification for client/server functions.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Removed cdsv global variable This_connect.  It is now passed as a parameter where needed.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added two new functions to listmgr.c to reduce the need for malloc() and free() of list heads.
\par }\pard \s32\widctlpar\adjustright {
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {09-26-96 CDS fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {
Slightly better handling of the Event Log.  Almost all messages are now message #1, which is not optimal.   The event source and message types are not \ldblquote unknown\rdblquote  anymore.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright {
Cdsv.exe automatically sets up the application event log registry values that are required.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright {The superfluous \ldblquote 
Going down at hh:mm:ss message is no longer appended to the event log.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {09-25-96 CDS fix (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \fi-360\li360\sa120\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \fs20\cgrid {
There was a problem dealing with corrupt indexes.  If the tempdir was null, CDS would attempt to move the corrupt index onto itself.  Now the corrupt index will always have a suffix of id-, rather than idx.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {09-16-96 CDS fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed cdinstsv to allow starting servers that are not for MOACURPROJ project by properly getting service registry parameters.
\par }\pard \s32\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl12\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\ilvl12\adjustright {
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright {
Enhanced cdsv.exe to halt with a message during initialization  when the tables directory is remotely mounted.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {09-15-96 CDS fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {Don
\rquote t post a NOT_RUN after killing a server because there is already a server running on the same directory.   Followed Bruce Oscarson\rquote s code for R1V2.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {09-13-96 CDS enhancement (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added more fields used by cdsv to the minimum dictionary in \\moa\\ibamindd.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Extended the newflds file use for upgrading to the V1.4 CDS.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {09-11-96 CDS tcl makefile  fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Changed all executables to use resource for version info and to use cdscl.dll for smaller footprint. 
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Changed to compile and link with MSVC++ 4.2.   Includes changes to DLLs. 
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {09-08-96 CDS fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Support hexadecimal constants in ASCII where clause criteria.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}zero length is same as NULL_VALUE for FT_BULK, FT_DATE, and FT_IND fields.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed bug in comparison of two FT_IND values.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed bug in support of \ldblquote not null\rdblquote  and \ldblquote null Ok\rdblquote  in table definitions.   The bug appeared during insert and update.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Support window handle in cds environment control block on clients.  This allows the CDS processing to use a different window than other parts 
of a process.   Global window handles are no longer used.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Don\rquote t raise an error when a client closes a context that has no remote (server-side) pointer.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Fixed bug in use of hexdmp() when printing a cds record for debugging.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {09-02-96 CDS fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {Fixed
 bugs in logdump.exe that caused crashes when trying to print database record contents.   Now using WriteFile() instead of printf().
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {08-29-96 CDS log timer (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Increased the maximum time allowed for the logging thread to complete a log write from 3 seconds to 10.  In some extreme cases, 3 was not enough, and when this timer expires, CDS fails hard (NOT_RUN). 
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {08-23-96 CDS client bug fix (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fix bug of rotating table buffer size on client side for newly created tables.   Size was wrong only on client side and only for the task that created the table.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {08-05-96 CDS client change (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Change in client to eliminate possibility of CDS connect request looping when we get an unexpected error code from MCNConnectService.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {08-01-96 CDSimport enhancement (bjo)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added support for conversion from ASCII to NUMERIC during import.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {07-21-96 CDS  changes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Fixed usage statement response to cdsclrlg -U.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added new messages to err_5200 about the new \lquote fields\rquote  table.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added MSVCR40D.dll to cdsodbc setup.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added prevention of direct update of the fields meta-table.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}changed cdinstsv, cdsreasn, and prcaptur to use resource for version info.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {06-26-96 CDS  changes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Increased maximum index trees per table from 20 to 30 on the NT version.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {06-25-96 CDSV.EXE changes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added File Manager visible version resource.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {06-25-96 CDS NOTES
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Changed name of manual from CDS NOTES to \ldblquote CDS Programmer\rquote s Reference\rdblquote , as requested by Q/A to avoid confusion with the release notes document.
\par }\pard\plain \s31\sb240\sa60\keepn\widctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 {\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright \b\f1\cgrid {06-13-96 CDS Setup fixes (s)
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard\plain \s32\fi-360\li360\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright \f1\fs20\cgrid {
Added msvc40d.dll to moasrvr.fil because putreg.exe uses it.   The install puts it in \\moa\\bin.  It ordinarily resides in \\winnt35\\system32.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Deleted superfluous include files from moasrvr.fil.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added cdscl.dll to moasrvr.fil.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}Added new fields to ibamindd\\fld file and DDOBJ.*
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\s32 \f14\fs20\cf10\cgrid \loch\af14\dbch\af0\hich\f14 \'fc\tab}}\pard \s32\fi-360\li1080\widctlpar{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls6\pnrnot0\pncf10\pnf14\pnstart1\pnindent360\pnhang{\pntxtb \'fc}}\ls6\adjustright {
CdsFldSeq INT 4 [ ] SCDEascuRDmpbdh 0 0 0 0 0 0 0 
